SIMPLE: imprescriptible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imprescriptible
<hw>Im`pre*scrip"ti*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>prescriptible</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>imprescriptible</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not capable of being
lost or impaired by neglect, by disuse, or by the claims of another
founded on prescription; -- of rights.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The right of navigation, fishing, and others that may be exercised
on the sea, belonging to the right of mere ability, are
<qex>imprescriptible</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Vattel (Trans. )</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not derived from, or dependent on, external
authority; self-evidencing; obvious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>imprescriptible</qex> laws of the pure reason.</q>
<rj><qau>Colerridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imprescriptibly</ent>⟦br⟧
